From 45bff8a8be006d318dfe3921e21233dd477161d3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Tue, 5 May 2026 10:28:23 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 8 polish: storyboard design pass

Brings the Storyboard sub-mode visually closer to the demo:

- Edge labels: every dependency arrow now carries a 'depends on'
  pill at its midpoint, with hover-aware accent styling.
- Bigger card layout (248x156): top tier-coloured stripe, mono
  'ch NN' chapter badge, caution glyph, in-card reviewed
  checkbox, 2-line clamped title, 3-line clamped summary, mono
  footer with file count + plus/minus.
- Rounded Manhattan edges: quadratic-curve corners replace the
  prior sharp 90-degree turns.
- Click-and-drag panning on the canvas (skips clicks that
  originate inside interactive children).
- Wider detail rail (360px) with file chips, Connections
  section listing 'depends on' rows for both directions, Key
  points list, sensitive callout, and a Mark/Unmark reviewed
  button.
- Header chip with reviewed count, single-entry edge legend,
  dotted-grid canvas background.
